## Harness-OS MCP Tools

These are the 31 MCP tools available through the harness server. Tools are organized by domain and callable directly by the agent.

### Session Lifecycle

| Action | Tool | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Start new session | `session_start({ repo_path })` | Returns session_id + pending tasks |
| Resume existing session | `session_resume({ repo_path })` | Alias for session_start with continue semantics |
| End without handoff | `session_end({ session_id })` | Use only if no handoff is needed |
| End with full handoff | `session_handoff({ session_id, summary, unfinished, next_steps })` | Always preferred — writes handoff + progress atomically |

### Task Management

| Action | Tool | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Create task | `task_create({ title, scope, session_id })` | scope limits file access for this task |
| Update task status | `task_update({ task_id, status })` | status: pending/in-progress/done/blocked |
| List tasks | `task_list({ repo_path, status })` | Filter by status to find next work item |

### Verification & Quality

| Action | Tool | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Full verification | `verify_run({ repo_path, steps, task_id })` | Runs install → build → test → lint |
| Save evidence | `verify_run` with `task_id` | Evidence auto-saved when task_id is provided |

### Skills & Learning

| Action | Tool | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Load a skill | `skill_load({ name })` | Returns skill markdown content |
| List skills | `skill_list({ stack_filter })` | Filter by stack (node, dotnet, etc.) |
| Suggest skills | `skill_suggest({ task_title, stack })` | Let harness find relevant skills |
| Create skill from session | `skill_create_from_session({ session_id, theme })` | Generate SKILL.md draft from audit log |

### Instincts (Pattern Memory)

| Action | Tool | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Get learned instincts | `instinct_get({ tags, min_confidence })` | Filter by tags to find relevant patterns |
| Add a new instinct | `instinct_add({ description, tags })` | Document a pattern for future sessions |
| Record outcome | `instinct_record_outcomes({ session_id, outcome })` | outcome: success/failure |
| Prune instincts | `instinct_prune({ confidence_below, dry_run })` | Use dry_run first to preview |
| Evolve to skill | `instinct_evolve({ tag_cluster })` | Needs 5+ instincts in a cluster |
| Promote instinct | `instinct_promote({ instinct_id })` | Make pending instinct permanent |

### Scope & Boundaries

| Action | Tool | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Check file scope | `scope_check({ repo_path, file_path, task_id })` | Check before editing any file |
| Get scope config | `scope_get({ repo_path, task_id })` | View allowed/forbidden paths |

